  "number": 1227,
  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/1227",
  "title": "API Proposal - non numeric counts on refinementList et al",
  "body": "I'm using (and loving) instantsearch.js for the project I'm working on but I've hit a limitation that doesn't seem necessary.\n\nI have a lot of results to filter/facet, and when presenting the refinementList options to the user instead of showing \"Archived (103,256)\" I want to present it as \"Archived (100k+)\". This is better UX as there is less parsing required to understand the size of the result set. I actually plan to break it down into a range of steps.\n\nI've tried to use the transformData mechanism on the refinementList widget which _would work_ if it weren't for the fact that the number is then manipulated as an integer further down the chain causing \"NaN\" to be output.\n\nIt feels like there shouldn't be any need to modify that value so it should end up intact in the output. Another option would be to allow something like an \"overrideCount\" property to be added to the object in the transformData method which would be used instead if present.\n",
